{"number":3,"verseCount":18,"verses":[[1,["My brethren, ",["be",["study-note-ref","a",["JST James 3:1 … strive not for the mastery, knowing that in so doing we shall receive the greater condemnation."]]]," not many ",["masters",["study-note-ref","b",["GR (also) teachers."]]],", knowing that we shall ",["receive",["study-note-ref","c",[["D&C 82:3","dc-testament/dc/82.3"],"."]]]," the greater condemnation."]],[2,["For in many things we ",["offend all",["study-note-ref","a",["GR stumble, err."]]],". If any man ",["offend not",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Offense","tg/offense"],"."]]]," in ",["word",["study-note-ref","c",[["Ps. 39:1","ot/ps/39.1"],"; ",["Prov. 21:23","ot/prov/21.23"],"."]]],", the ",["",1541],"same ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," a ",["perfect",["study-note-ref","d",[["TG Perfection","tg/perfection"],"."]]]," man, ",["and",["clarity-word"]]," able also to bridle the whole body."]],[3,["Behold, we put bits in the horses’ mouths, that they may obey us; and we turn about their whole body."]],[4,["Behold also the ships, which though ",["they be",["clarity-word"]]," so great, and ",["are",["clarity-word"]]," driven of fierce winds, yet are they turned about with a very small helm, whithersoever the ",["governor",["study-note-ref","a",["GR helmsman, pilot."]]]," listeth."]],[5,["Even so the tongue is a little member, and ",["boasteth",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Boast","tg/boast"],"; ",["Rashness","tg/rashness"],"."]]]," great things. Behold, how great a ",["matter",["study-note-ref","b",["GR forest."]]]," a little fire kindleth!"]],[6,["And the ",["tongue",["study-note-ref","a",[["Prov. 16:27","ot/prov/16.27"],"; ",["Mark 7:20 (19–23)","nt/mark/7.20"],"; ",["Alma 12:14","bofm/alma/12.14"],"; ",["D&C 88:121","dc-testament/dc/88.121"],"."]]]," ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," a fire, a world of iniquity: so is the tongue among our members, that it defileth the whole body, and setteth on fire the course of nature; and it is set on fire of hell."]],[7,["For every kind of beasts, and of birds, and of serpents, and of things in the sea, is tamed, and hath been tamed of mankind:"]],[8,["But the ",["tongue",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Gossip","tg/gossip"],"; ",["Profanity","tg/profanity"],"."]]]," can no man tame; ",["it is",["clarity-word"]]," an ",["unruly",["study-note-ref","b",["GR untameable, uncontrollable."]]]," evil, full of deadly poison."]],[9,["Therewith bless we God, even the Father; and therewith ",["curse",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Curse","tg/curse"],"."]]]," we men, which are made after the ",["similitude",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG God, Body of, Corporeal Nature","tg/god-body-of-corporeal-nature"],"."]]]," of God."]],[10,["Out of the same ",["mouth",["study-note-ref","a",[["Matt. 12:34","nt/matt/12.34"],"; ",["Luke 6:45","nt/luke/6.45"],". ",["TG Hypocrisy","tg/hypocrisy"],"."]]]," proceedeth blessing and cursing. My brethren, these things ought not so to be."]],[11,["Doth a ",["fountain",["study-note-ref","a",["GR spring, well. ",["Moro. 7:11 (6–11)","bofm/moro/7.11"],"."]]]," send forth at the same place sweet ",["water",["clarity-word"]]," and bitter?"]],[12,["Can the fig tree, my brethren, bear olive berries? either a vine, figs? so ",["can",["clarity-word"]]," no fountain both yield salt water and fresh."]],[13,["Who ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," a wise man and endued with knowledge among you? let him shew out of a good ",["conversation",["study-note-ref","a",[["Prov. 12:13 (13–19)","ot/prov/12.13"],"."]]]," his works with ",["meekness",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Meek","tg/meek"],"."]]]," of wisdom."]],[14,["But if ye have bitter envying and ",["strife",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Strife","tg/strife"],"."]]]," in your hearts, ",["glory not",["study-note-ref","b",["GR do not assume superiority over."]]],", and lie not against the truth."]],[15,["This wisdom descendeth not from above, but ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," earthly, sensual, devilish."]],[16,["For where ",["envying",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Envy","tg/envy"],"."]]]," and ",["strife",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Contention","tg/contention"],"."]]]," ",["is,",["clarity-word"]]," there ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," confusion and every evil work."]],[17,["But the ",["wisdom",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG God, Intelligence of","tg/god-intelligence-of"],"; ",["Wisdom","tg/wisdom"],"."]]]," that is from above is first pure, then peaceable, gentle, ",["and",["clarity-word"]]," ",["easy to be entreated",["study-note-ref","b",["GR pliant, easily persuaded."]]],", full of ",["mercy",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG God, Mercy of","tg/god-mercy-of"],"."]]]," and good fruits, without partiality, and without ",["hypocrisy",["study-note-ref","d",[["D&C 121:42","dc-testament/dc/121.42"],"."]]],"."]],[18,["And the fruit of ",["righteousness",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Righteousness","tg/righteousness"],"."]]]," is sown in ",["peace",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Peace","tg/peace"],"; ",["Peace of God","tg/peace-of-god"],"."]]]," of them that make ",["peace",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Peacemakers","tg/peacemakers"],"."]]],"."]]],"volume":"nt"}